{{Infobox NRHP | name =Hutzler Brothers Palace Building | nrhp_type = | image = Hutzler Bros Baltimore 1.JPG | caption = Hutzler Brothers Palace Building, March 2012 | location= 210-218 N. Howard St., [[Baltimore, Maryland]] | coordinates = {{coord|39|17|32|N|76|37|10.6|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = United States Baltimore#Maryland#USA | built = {{Start date|1888}} | architect = [[Baldwin & Pennington]]; Edmunds, James R. | architecture = Second Empire, Modern Movement | added = June 7, 1984 | area = {{convert|0.2|acre}} | governing_body = Private | refnum = 84001348<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }}
The '''Hutzler Brothers Palace Building''' is a historic [[flagship]] [[department store]] building located at [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]], [[United States]] and built by [[Hutzler's]]. It was constructed in 1888, with a south bay added in 1924.
The original limestone [[Romanesque Revival|Romanesque]] eclectic façade is three bays wide and five stories in height. The ground floor façade was redesigned in 1931 in the [[Art Moderne]] style. Hutzler's is believed to hold the record for longevity in an original location among American department stores, having been founded on this site in 1858.<ref name="mht_ihp">{{cite web|url=https://mht.maryland.gov/secure/medusa/PDF/NR_PDFs/NR-800.pdf |title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Hutzler Brothers Palace Building|date=March 1983|accessdate=2016-03-01 |author=Peter Kurtze and Edward Perlman|publisher=Maryland Historical Trust}}</ref>
[[File:Hutzler Bros Baltimore 2.JPG|thumb|Hutzler Bros. building in Baltimore]] Hutzler Brothers Palace Building was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1984.<ref name="nris"/>
